Times," Ruben Martinez has scheduled a Ventura poetry reading Wednesday. . . . 
Martinez, 29, will discuss his Salvadoran and Mexican heritage and his book -- 
"The Other Side: Notes From the New L.A., Mexico City and Beyond." . . . "We're 
primarily interested in books as items of culture, not bricks that go over the 
counter for 12 bucks apiece," Ventura Bookstore co-owner Ed Elrod said. 
