<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; USC; MCCULLOUGH LEADING JUNIOR COLLEGE TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saladin McCullough, the All-CIF running back from Pasadena Muir High who in 
1993 signed a letter of intent to attend USC, is lighting up junior college 
football for Pasadena City College.  
</P>
<P>
 After two games, his coach, Dennis Gossard, said of him Monday: "There is no 
better runner in college football, at any level, than this kid.He's a great 
back, he's going to get better and he still wants to play for SC." 
</P>
<P>
 McCullough, 5-9 and 175 pounds, has more than 500 yards total offense in two 
games. Saturday against Golden West he had 255 combined yards. He also had a 
70-yard touchdown run called back. 
</P>
<P>
 McCullough sat out last year while his Scholastic Aptitude Test score was 
challenged. He lost his case in arbitration. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
