<P>
COSTA MESA GOLFER SHARES SENIOR LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Housen of Brielle, N.J., and Dennis Iden of Costa Mesa shot 2-under-par 
70s on Monday to share the first-round lead in qualifying for the 40th USGA 
Senior Amateur Championship in Nicholasville, Ky. 
</P>
<P>
 Iden, a 59-year-old salesman and former professional bowler, finished with 
birdies on three of his final four holes. 
</P>
<P>
 The low 64 after today's second round advance to match play. 
</P>
