PREP ROUNDUP; BREA-OLINDA WINS IN GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda swept at No. 1 and No. 2 doubles to key a 13-5 victory over 
Glendora in a nonleague girls' tennis match Monday at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 Beth St. Clair and Brandy Cheney won, 6-1, 6-0, 6-2, at No. 1 and Meghan Walsh 
and Kristin Schmactenberg won, 7-5, 6-4, 6-1, at No. 2 for Brea (4-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 11, Los Amigos 7 -- Suzanne Nguyen swept her sets for Saddleback 
(2-0), winning, 6-1, 6-1, 6-0. Teammate Cyndi Cao also swept in singles, 6-1, 
6-4, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 11, Troy 7 -- Jessica Wilson swept her sets, 6-0, 6-2, 6-3, to lead 
Valencia (1-3) to victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 3, La Quinta 0 -- Heather Cunningham had nine kills in the 15-1, 15-9, 
15-9 victory for Kennedy (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 19, Savanna 12 -- Ryan Christensen scored 10 goals and Jeff Gorman 
added five for host Orange (3-4). Cliff Popper scored seven goals for Savanna. 
</P>
