<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; SCC MEN'S SOCCER BEATS SAN DIEGO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California College, despite being severely out-shot, upset San Diego 
State, 1-0, in a men's soccer game Monday in San Diego. Southern California is 
an NAIA team and San Diego State is a Division I program. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Villar scored the only goal on a penalty kick with about 10 minutes 
left. Villar is a sophomore from Tustin High and Orange Coast. His goal was one 
of four shots SCC took. San Diego State was much more active around the net, 
getting 20 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Brent Rogers had eight saves for SCC (3-3). Bret Weaver had no saves for San 
Diego State (4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 5, California Lutheran 4 (OT) -- Jason Hespedales scored with two 
minutes left in overtime for visiting Chapman (4-1-1). Armando Orizaba had two 
goals for Chapman, which trailed at the half, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 3, Caltech 0 -- Freshman Chris Kneip scored three goals for visiting 
Concordia (3-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In California Coastal Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Christian 4, Cal Maritime 3 -- Ryan Bean scored three goals and Bryce 
Ginther scored one for Pacific Christian (5-0). Adrian Siebeinhaar scored three 
goals, two on penalty kicks, for Cal Maritime (0-3). 
</P>
