BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY & TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Micron Technology's Top Officers Quit: In a move that mystified industry 
observers, Boise, Ida.-based semiconductor maker Micron Technology Inc. said 
that its top three executives would resign sometime over the next month for 
"personal reasons." Leaving the company will be Joe Parkinson, chief executive 
and co-founder; Jim Garrett, president and chief operating officer, and Reid 
Langrill, chief financial officer. The company also announced that Steve 
Appleton will take over as chief executive. Appleton worked his way up from 
production-line worker to become CEO of Micron Semiconductor, a subsidiary that 
accounts for 89% of Micron Technology's sales. 
</P>
