<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; MOSS TO APPEAL FINE FOR SEATTLE FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Linebacker Winston Moss, one of eight Raiders fined for a fight against the 
Seattle Seahawks a week ago, plans to appeal the $7,500 judgment levied against 
him by the league. 
</P>
<P>
 Those fined included defensive back Derrick Hoskins ($6,500) and defensive 
linemen Chester McGlockton ($4,000), Aundray Bruce ($4,000) and Anthony Smith 
($2,500).Three others, whose identities were not revealed, were fined $2,500 
each for being in the area of the fight, bringing the total Raider bill to 
$32,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Nine Seahawks were fined a total of $27,000. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders, who led the league in penalties a year ago and were off to 
another big start with 19 penalties for 125 yards in the first two games, had 
another 10 for 118 yards Sunday against Denver. 
</P>
<P>
 But 42 of those yards came on a controversial pass interference call against 
cornerback Lionel Washington. 
</P>
<P>
 And there was little of the pushing and shoving that has characterized many 
previous Raider-Bronco games. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
