<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some Banks Fail to Warn Fund Investors, Agency Says: The Office of the 
Comptroller of the Currency said some banks continue to do a poor job of giving 
investors written warning that the mutual funds and other investments bankers 
sell are not federally insured and could go sour. The government review shows 
that many of the marketing and advertising materials voluntarily turned over by 
more than 700 national banks for OCC review violated federal banking guidelines 
issued last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
