<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK: PREP EXTRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anna-Kaisa Niemi 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 With 1993 All-County performer Jessica Corbin sidelined with a hip injury, 
Irvine looked elsewhere for leadership Saturday at the Newport-Irvine Rotary 
Club Invitational at Woodbridge High. The Vaqueros got it from Niemi, an 
exchange student from Finland, who finished third in 18 minutes 33 seconds to 
help Irvine edge Palos Verdes Peninsula, ranked No. 2 in the section Division I 
preseason poll, in the Division I race."I really think as she gains confidence, 
she's going to continue to improve and move on up," Irvine Coach Randy Rossi 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Tracy Clark: Corona del Mar, junior. Finished first in the Division IV race at 
Woodbridge, leading the Sea Kings to the team title. 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Danielle Brandlin & Melissa Rosenthal: Los Alamitos. Each won her final two 
singles sets at love to lead unranked Griffins to a 76-66 victory in games over 
then-No. 7 Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Marcy Crouch: Marina, senior. Had 28 kills as the unranked Vikings beat 
then-No. 6 Mater Dei in four games. 
</P>
<P>
 Misty May: Newport Harbor, senior. Had 29 kills, including nine in decisive 
game, in the top-ranked Sailors' 15-17, 17-15, 15-4 victory over Laguna Beach 
in the Orange County Division I championship match. 
</P>
