<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; PORN ACTRESS PLEADS GUILTY IN 
MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 45-year-old Newbury Park porn actress will probably get probation after 
pleading guilty to molesting a 14-year-old boy, a prosecutor said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty.Tom Connors said that Laurie Arden pleaded guilty Friday to 
four felony charges stemming from two sexual encounters she had with the 
teen-ager in April and May. 
</P>
<P>
 Arden pleaded guilty to two counts of unlawful sexual intercourse with a 
minor, one count of sexual penetration with a foreign object and one count of 
showing explicit photos to a minor. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other criminal counts against her will be dismissed at sentencing Oct. 17, 
Connors said. Superior Court Judge Charles W. Campbell Jr. has agreed to place 
Arden on probation as long as no additional victims come forward prior to 
sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
 Arden was arrested at the E-Z 8 Motel in Newbury Park on July 27 after the 
14-year-old boy told police about his two sexual encounters with Arden. Arden 
hired the boy through a youth-employment center to help her move from a rented 
room on White Oak Lane. 
</P>
<P>
 At a preliminary hearing last month, the victim testified that he agreed to 
have sex with Arden in April because he was curious. In May, however, he said 
she forced him to have sex with her by threatening to report their previous 
sexual encounter to police. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy also testified that Arden showed him images on a computer screen and 
in magazines of nude women, including herself. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
