<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; PLAYGROUND PUT OFF FOR LACK OF FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Short of money to buy lumber and other supplies, the group raising funds to 
build a community playground at Blanche Reynolds School in midtown Ventura has 
postponed its construction date from November until early March. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers for the planned Rainbow Bridge Community Playground, which will be 
built at the school but open to the public, said they have raised more than 
$40,000 in cash and materials but need $60,000 more. 
</P>
<P>
 The postponement will give organizers more time to hold fund-raisers and apply 
for corporate grants, Blanche Reynolds teacher Lisa Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It just gives us a little more time," Hall said. "Now we feel like a burden 
has been lifted off our shoulders." 
</P>
<P>
 As envisioned, a corps of 1,500 parents, teachers and other volunteers will 
build the playground by hand over five days. 
</P>
<P>
 To volunteer or to donate money or supplies, call Hall at 641-5409. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
