WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR TOURISM CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are being sought to greet visitors who stop by the Oxnard tourism 
bureau's new office at the Oxnard Factory Outlet. 
</P>
<P>
 Carol Lavender, executive director of the tourism bureau, said she is looking 
for as many as 60 people to work in the center providing information to those 
who stop in. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is a responsible position," Lavender said. "And it gives the volunteers a 
chance to meet the public and be helpful in a number of different situations." 
</P>
<P>
 Lavender said the volunteers would work about four hours at a time at the 
factory outlet office, which she said attracted more than 5,000 people in June, 
the month it opened. 
</P>
<P>
 "They pretty much act as an ambassador to Oxnard by giving people the 
information they are requesting about the area, where to shop or where to stay 
while they're visiting," she said of the volunteers. 
</P>
<P>
 Without an increase in the number of volunteers at the tourism center, the 
center may have to cut its hours of operation, Lavender said. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently the office is open from 11 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. seven days a week. For 
more information or to volunteer, call 385-7545. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
