VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW / JACK SEARLES: BRIEFLY: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ojai Valley Inn hopes to increase its appeal to women with a $16-million 
renovation that would include a new health spa and up to 60 additional guest 
rooms. The spa, featuring a beauty salon, aerobics studios and massage rooms, 
appears to have a good chance of getting the required permits.The new guest 
rooms, however, will have to overcome the Ojai area's tough slow-growth rules. 
. . . An Oxnard attorney, Gregory J. Ramirez, is co-chairman of an American 
Trial Lawyers Assn. group investigating the failure of orthopedic implants, 
including the alleged non-approved use of spinal screws. Ramirez says he's been 
receiving an average of six calls a day about the screws since they were 
featured on the TV program "20/20." 
