<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; CITY MAY EASE RULES ON USE OF CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Social clubs and hobby groups will be treated the same as other nonprofit 
organizations when it comes to using the Yorba Linda Community Center under a 
policy the City Council will consider tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, only groups that have a narrowly defined tax-exempt status from the 
state qualify as nonprofit organizations. The city gives 12 free uses per 
calendar year of the community center to nonprofit groups and charges them 
lower fees for additional uses. 
</P>
<P>
 While many groups benefit from the policy, others complain that it excludes 
them because they lack tax-exempt status. DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
