<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; COUNCIL TO CONSIDER SUPPORT OF PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council tonight will consider support of the statewide initiative 
seeking to bar illegal immigrants from receiving public education, 
non-emergency health care and social services. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Mark Leyes, who is seeking reelection, has asked the council to 
discuss Proposition 187, which will go before voters in November. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Bruce A. Broadwater, who is running for mayor, also wants the 
council to consider resolutions asking the federal government to share the cost 
to resettle immigrants, curb illegal immigration and adopt new policies to 
assist cities affected by illegal immigration. 
</P>
<P>
 Several Orange County cities, including Westminster and Huntington Beach, have 
passed similar resolutions in the past. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
