COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE; HEARING ON REPRIMAND IS DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A public hearing on a reprimand stemming from sexual harassment charges was 
postponed Monday by officials of the Orange Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 A new date for the hearing of chief fiscal officer Joyce Capelle -- accused 
last December of tolerating sexual harassment in the workplace -- has not been 
set, according to Supt. Robert L. French. 
</P>
<P>
 The Board of Education had dropped charges against Capelle in August, but she 
had requested a public hearing on a letter of reprimand that board members 
proposed to put in her file. 
</P>
<P>
 The board also postponed a closed discussion of a defamation suit filed by 
Capelle and two other administrators involved in the scandal. LESLEY WRIGHT 
