<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SCIENCE MENTOR PROGRAM IS OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Science-By-Mail, a national pen pal mentor program for children in grades four 
through nine, is accepting applications through Oct. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Throughout the school year, Science-By-Mail sends members three hands-on 
activity packets and links children with a volunteer scientist pen pal. 
</P>
<P>
 Members work on the experiments in the packets, communicating with their 
scientist pen-pal for ideas, advice and encouragement. 
</P>
<P>
 The topics for 1994-95 are weather, science magic and garbage. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 25,000 children and 2,000 scientists from around the world 
participate in the program, which costs $56 per membership group of one to four 
children. For more information, call (800) 729-3300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
