<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLAYING VICTIM FOUND IN ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was found shot to death Monday in a Canoga Park alley, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A resident of the 6700 block of Mason Avenue was on his way to work at about 
5:20 a.m. when he backed his car out of his driveway, "and there was this body 
laying there," said Detective Rick Swanston of the Los Angeles Police 
Department's West Valley station. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead man, identified as Edward Michael Garner, 21, of Canoga Park, had 
been shot several times in the head, Swanston said. Police suspect he may have 
been a robbery victim because his pockets were turned out and his wallet was 
missing when he was found. 
</P>
<P>
 The alley also was the subject of recent narcotics investigations, Swanston 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police thought Garner was killed sometime between midnight and 3 a.m., when 
neighbors said they heard several gunshots. No one called police, however, 
until the body was discovered by the commuter, Swanston said. 
</P>
