<P>
CASA YOUTH SHELTER, SPORTS PROGRAM GET COUNTY GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Casa Youth Shelter last week received a $2,500 county grant to help support 
the shelter's art therapy counseling program for troubled teen-agers. 
</P>
<P>
 Supervisor Harriett M. Wieder presented the check to Myldred Jones, who 
founded Casa Youth Shelter in 1978. It provides a residence for youths 12 to 17 
who have run away from home or are having problems with their parents. 
</P>
<P>
 The shelter has served more than 7,000 youths and reunited 85% of them with 
their families. Wieder presented the check during the shelter's annual 
fund-raiser at the Disneyland Hotel in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Save Our Youth, a nonprofit group that provides sports, fitness and 
recreational programs for teen-agers in Costa Mesa, also received $5,000 from 
the county's social program grant. 
</P>
