<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PAY-FONE SYSTEMS REPORTS PROFIT TURNAROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pay-Fone Systems Inc., a Van Nuys-based provider of automated 
payroll-processing services, reported a profit in its fiscal fourth quarter 
after a loss in the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months ended June 30, Pay-Fone earned $21,526 while its operating 
revenue rose 8%, to $1.09 million.A year before, the company lost $49,720 on 
operating revenue of $1.01 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the fiscal year, Pay-Fone reported net income of $188,966, a 25% increase 
from its $151,015 profit in fiscal 1993. Its annual operating revenue was $4.46 
million, off slightly from $4.51 million in the prior year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed part of its revenue and earnings growth to its February 
acquisition of Concentric Computer Corp. and added that it is seeking other 
acquisitions or alliances. 
</P>
