<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RESTAURANTS AND RETAIL; RALPHS, FOOD 4 LESS EMPLOYEES WONDER WHERE 
THEY'LL WORK AFTER THE MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Supermarket signs aren't the only things changing now that Ralphs Grocery Co., 
headquartered in Compton, is being merged with La Habra-based Food 4 Less. 
</P>
<P>
 During a Friday news conference at the Food 4 Less headquarters building, a 
handful of employees acknowledged that they're uncertain where they'll be 
working after the merger. 
</P>
<P>
 But a number of jobs will be transferred to Ralph's massive Compton 
headquarters and warehouse facility. Food 4 Less President and Chief Operating 
Officer George Golleher, who's been named vice chairman of the merged 
companies, will be making the drive to Compton as the chains are consolidated. 
</P>
<P>
 Golleher now faces a 90-mile round trip from his Laguna Beach home to the La 
Habra office. The commute to Compton will be four miles shorter, but Golleher 
said he expects the traffic to be noticeably heavier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
