<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RESTAURANTS AND RETAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Honored Twice: John Martin, chairman and chief executive officer of the Taco 
Bell Corp., is being honored for his innovative ways by two diverse 
organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 He will be honored by the Multi-unit Foodservice Operators group today during 
its annual meeting in New Orleans.Martin will speak at the meeting on "how 
leaders kindle entrepreneurial spirit, and how innovation often comes from the 
middle of organizations, not always from the top down," said Taco Bell 
spokeswoman Janice Page. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Martin won the first Innovation In Hospitality Management Award 
presented by the Professional Development Institute of the School of Hotel and 
Restaurant Management at Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think it's a real indication of John Martin's creativity that he's being 
honored by both academia and the industry," said institute spokesman Tarun 
Kapoor. "We honored John for his innovations and as a person who's brought the 
concept of value to the hospitality industry." 
</P>
