<P>
 Cerplex Group Inc.: Shares of the Anaheim company gained a bit Monday from 
Friday's 21% drop caused by the company's report that revenue was slowing down. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's stock fell after it said that its repair contract with 
International Business Machines Corp. would result in lower-than-expected 
third-quarter net income of about $1 million, or 7 cents to 8 cents a share. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerplex, which provides repairs on IBM machines, said late Thursday that it 
expects its revenue shortfall from IBM will continue into the fourth quarter, 
which ends Dec. 31, but that it should be offset by increasing revenue from new 
programs. 
</P>
<P>
 On Friday, Cerplex stock fell $3 a share to close at $11.25 a share in heavy 
trading, making it the third-largest percentage loser on the Nasdaq system. On 
Monday, the stock rose 25 cents a share to close at $11.50 a share. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerplex provides electronic repair services and distributes electronic 
components. The company said IBM revenue fell about $7 million in the current 
quarter, although its overall revenue climbed to $32 million, up 68% from the 
year-ago period. 
</P>
