<P>
LAWSUIT AGAINST RAINBOW DISMISSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the plaintiffs' request, a federal district court in Santa Ana has 
dismissed a shareholders' lawsuit against Rainbow Technologies Inc. and some of 
its officers and directors, the company said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The suits were filed in December, after Rainbow reported lower-than-expected 
third-quarter results.The suits sought unspecified damages and alleged that the 
company and certain officers and directors violated federal securities laws in 
connection with various public statements, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rainbow Technologies said no payments or other considerations were made to the 
plaintiffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Founded in 1984, Rainbow Technologies is a leading supplier of 
software-protection devices and encryption technology for personal computers. 
The company had $35.1 million in sales last year. Rainbow's products are used 
by more than 10,000 software developers worldwide. 
</P>
<P>
 Rainbow's stock closed at $13 Monday, down 12.5 cents a share. 
