<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; A WALK ON THE BOULEVARD MAKES LIFE SO PRECIOUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When I was 69, I had cancer surgery. Up to then I did not know what "downtime" 
meant.The doctor advised me to walk as much as I could. In the beginning, I 
could walk only a few short blocks. Three years later I am walking three times 
a day and go much farther. Sunset Boulevard is my regular beat. Dog walkers, 
gardeners and postmen recognize me. I am getting stronger and healthier. My 
greatest pleasure is when I combine walking with garage sales on weekends. I 
now have enough paperbacks to last me into the next century. 
</P>
<P>
 -- SALLY BERMAN, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
